-- Citigroup gets Friday hearing before U.S. judge over Argentine bonds
-- By Nate Raymond in New York
-- Mon Sep 22, 2014 05:29PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Sept 22 (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc <C.N> is set to return to court Friday as it seeks to have a U.S. judge reconsider an order barring it from processing payments on $8.4 billion in bonds issued under Argentina's local laws following its 2002 default.

